title A yonder pass — 29 consumed and gated expanding-prompts folded to yonder/
prompt Keaton invited a yonder pass across the writings folders: fold to yonder/ anything generated before today or today that now sits a while ahead beyond the near-short-term roadmap, keeping near-term work one level deep, then continue where we left off.
think Chose the safest, most-aligned target rather than a broad sweep: expanding-prompts/ is the one folder whose own README already names yonder/ as the home for consumed prompts, and it had a large backlog of clearly-consumed execution prompts (the apply-* bench passes) and gated/superseded prompts sitting at the top level. The genuinely horizon design docs (Neth, Ojjo, warm-aura) and heavily-cited active docs stay put — this pass moved prompts whose work has landed or which are explicitly gated, not live design.
think Refused to move anything on age alone — measured living inbound references first. Wrote a helper that counts, per top-level prompt, references from living docs while excluding session-logs (immutable historical record, allowed to cite the pre-move path per the established pattern), work-in-progress/archive, the prompt itself, and the README index. Moved only the 29 with zero living references outside the README index, so no living promise breaks.
think Moved by git mv so history stays whole, then repointed every link the README index still held to a moved prompt (twelve rows: the recursion/infusion/final Brooke prompts, plus wov-dual-monarch-gated, mala-kind-field-gated, greencandy-root-lap2-reports, apply-cursor-bot-arc-audit), each now pointing at yonder/ and reworded to say consumed/in yonder. Verified twice with a staged-rename stale-link scan that no living doc still links a moved prompt at its old top-level path — CLEAN.
obs The 29 folded cleanly: apply-* execution passes (carriage, ns-l3 sync, resin batch, beading, recall, synthesis, tigerbeetle-alignment, parse-int, kumara extraction, kumara open-asks, realidream lane, spawn/wait-for, sh-migration, chain-read-seams, cursor-bot arc audit), the astrology-arc recursion/infusion/silo/fidelity prompts, the gated WOV/MALA/Greencandy prompts whose laps landed, the tablecloth-query device wire, the proven-seat G1 open prompt, and the urbit-fusion hammock reading set. The top level now shows near-term work first; the record stays whole in yonder/ and in the session logs.
think Left the deeper folders (external-research, active-designing) for a later, separately-verified pass — they carry higher citation density and more genuinely-live design, so a careful reference audit each deserves is its own sitting, not a tail-end sweep. Named that plainly rather than rush a risky move.
file expanding-prompts/yonder/ why: 29 consumed/gated prompts folded here by git mv, history whole
file expanding-prompts/README.md why: twelve index links repointed to yonder/, reworded consumed, date bumped
recommend keep-going — one clean, reference-verified yonder pass on the folder whose convention most directly calls for it; external-research/active-designing yonder passes remain available as their own careful sittings on Keaton's word.
